##Why is the new World Church raising the Red Flag in South Korea?

Weixin Signal Wowjiemian

Function introduction, the interface news is China has the influence original financial and economic new media, only serves the independent thinking crowd

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Workers disinfect a building behind the new World Church in Daegu, South Korea. Photo: Yonhap

REPORTER: Pan Jinhua

"This disease, which is the work of the devil, is designed to kill the growth of the new world. It is designed to destroy our progress, just as job was tested. "

Shortly after the South Korean health and epidemic prevention authorities notified the new coronavirus "super spread event" in the "new heaven and Earth Church" in Daegu city, tens of thousands of followers of the church passed an internal application, received this encouraging message from chairman Lee Man-Hee.

But they perhaps did not expect, this "test" , has come so fierce.

The total number of newly diagnosed cases of pneumonia reported in South Korea doubled for three consecutive days from February 19 to 22, from 51 to 433, eight times the previous figure. A total of 169 new cases were reported in South Korea on Tuesday, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 602 and deaths to 5.

Of these, as many as 329 are related to the new World Church in Taegu, representing 54.7 per cent. At least 111 people, including several health care workers and three deaths, were also infected at a hospital called Nant-le-grand in the town of Chongdo in North Gyeongsang, where the first infected devotee was found.

Even more worrying is that, starting on the 20th, with the new World Church as the starting point, the Korean epidemic is heading out of control, with new cases no longer confined to the Taegu and gyeongbuk regions, instead, it spread to Gyeongnam, Chungbuk, Huangchuan County, Seoul, Busan, Gyeonggi, Sejong the Great, Ulsan, Gangwon Province and other places. Cases linked to the church now cover more than half of Korea's administrative districts, and even the military has not been spared.

South Korea on the 23rd will be the new crown disease warning to the highest level: "serious. ". But until now, no one knew how the outbreak began at the new world church, and the first believer to be found infected, South Korea's case 31, had no overseas travel experience. But the trajectory of the 61-year-old Korean woman and the New World Church itself may provide some answers to these days of "out of control. ".

###The cult of the unique

According to a previous report by interface news, Case 31 had attended church services at New World Church in Taegu four times before her diagnosis. On the last two visits to church, she had developed symptoms such as cold and sore throat, there were 1,001 people who attended church services with her on both occasions.

Photographs of the Church's services show hundreds of devotees sitting in close proximity to one another in a relatively confined space, within two or three fists of one another.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The picture shows a very crowded church service in New World Church. Source: Photo provided by Reader to Korea daily

In fact, the so-called "Church" is located in an eight-story building in Daegu city. Married women and men sit on the fourth floor and seventh floor, while unmarried men and women sit on the eighth floor of the building where people gather for Sunday services, according to an anonymous follower, the South China Morning Post reported Thursday.

Before the service began, everyone had to sit "shoulder to shoulder, " with their masks and glasses off, followed by a Half-hour of chanting and an hour of sermons. At the end of the service, members of the congregation would break into small groups and greet each other, while married women would often share their prepared meals.

Lee Ho-yeon, who has been away from the church for five years, told The New York Times that, unlike other churches, Xintiandi requires its members to sit "like soldiers in the army" with nothing on their faces, sing as loud as you want.

In addition to this, worshippers also make some physical contact during the service, such as putting their arms around other people's shoulders, the The Korea Herald reported Thursday.

The combination of confined spaces and close contact makes it easy to imagine the scale of transmission once new coronavirus infections are introduced among the faithful, which can be spread by droplets and close contact.

In response, the new heaven and Earth Church gives the explanation is, "had to" . The church wrote on its website, "The media is saying that we are responsible for the spread of the virus and that we have a unique form of worship, but the truth is that we have to sit on the ground like this in order to accommodate more people in a limited space. "

The church told them not to be afraid of getting sick, said Ms. Lee. It is reported that case No. 31 refused to be transferred to a hospital at least twice before being diagnosed and refused to be tested for the new coronavirus.

"They tell us not to care about mundane things like work, pursuits or hobbies, " Ms. Lee said. "All our energy is spent proselytizing, even when we're sick. "

###The chosen ones

Still, the faithful stopped. The New World Church has announced that it will close the church in Taegu, banned access to its 74 churches in 12 branches across the country and urged worshippers to worship at home and online.

But that doesn't mean the new world church-related outbreak is over. According to its website, the church has more than 200,000 followers in South Korea and around the world, including churches and affiliated institutions. The Church has about 1,100 strongholds in South Korea, and not only does it communicate with each other, but its followers are spread across all walks of life.

The South China Morning Post pointed out that in Daegu, a city of 2.5 million people, for example, 13,000 people are believers in Xintiandi. In Japan, mainland China, Hong Kong and about 30 countries and regions, including some Southeast Asian countries, and some 20,000 followers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Source: New World Church website

According to public records, the full name of the New World Church is "the temple of the proof Tabernacle of the new world Jesus Church" , established by 88-year-old Korean Lee Man-Hee on March 14,1984, and is headquartered in Gocheon city, Gyeonggi Province.

Lee Man-Hee was born on September 15,1931, in Gyeongsang Province, South Korea. According to South Korea's joongang Ilbo newspaper on the 21st, gyeongbuk-do-gyeongbuk is the hometown of Lee Man-Hee and is known as the three holy places of the new Heaven Church along with Gwacheon and Jilongshan Gushifeng (where Lee Man-Hee is said to have practiced) in Chungnam.

From January 31 to February 2, Lee Man-Hee's brother's funeral was held at the Great South Hospital in Qingdaojun, and there were presumably quite a few Xintiandi devotees present. However, case 31 says she did not attend the funeral, but she did go to a bathhouse in Cheongdo County.

According to its website, "new heaven and earth" is the Kingdom of God, created on Earth by God to fulfill the will of Heaven, which has been done for 6,000 years. Lee Man-Hee is the "ordained minister" who is creating the Kingdom of God on earth and will witness the "apocalypse" and "new heaven and New Earth" predicted in the book of revelation.

In his book, the Path I have traveled and the grace of God, which is said to be Lee Man-Hee's autobiography, he wrote, "I am a descendant of the royal family, and came into this world as light, and one day I met Jesus, who fell from the sky. " "I have walked with a rainbow everywhere I have walked with a cross (cloud) and with light. ".

"The followers of Xintiandi believe that Lee Man-Hee is immortal and can live forever, " Ji-il Tark, a professor at Changshen University in Busan, told the Associated Press, according to the Church's website, "At the time of the final judgment, 144,000 people will be able to become one and go to heaven. ".

Hong Yeun-ho's daughter joined the New World Church two years ago. He told the Bloomberg L.P. that only after completing a six month course could he officially join the Church and attend its services. In addition, all members of the congregation must be fingerprinted in order to enter the church. It makes them feel "chosen, " says Hong.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On November 10 last year, the new World Church held a grand graduation ceremony. Source: New World Church website

And every major event, the Church of new heaven and earth will be out of the million people. On November 10 last year, the Church held a high-profile "graduation ceremony" to celebrate the successful completion of the six-month programme by 103764 members of the congregation. Due to the large number of people, the new World Church had to adopt a live broadcast format, in many places at the same time for the ceremony.

###"Secrecy" and controversy

South Korea's "East Asia daily" reported on the 20th, the new World Church this close religious ties, will greatly change the trend of the new pneumonia epidemic. "In the new world church, hundreds of thousands of people gather in one place to worship, eat and talk, and the virus can cause infection in a very short time, " a religious expert told the newspaper

This is illustrated by the dramatic increase in the number of cases associated with the new world church in Taegu. According to a report by the Korea Times on the 21st, the city of Daegu added 3,474 worshippers to the survey of 1,001 people who attended church services with case No. 31 on the 9th and 16th of this month, 544 people have reported symptoms, and 343 remain unreachable.

As South Korea's central epidemic prevention department expanded the scope of testing, as of the 22nd day, the Church has 9,336 people have been questioned, of which 1,261 said they felt unwell, the proportion is as high as 13.5% .

But South Korean clerics suspect that the true number of people at risk of infection is only going to be higher, and not just within the new World Church.

The Pastor, Shin Hyun-uk, told the South China Morning Post that the Church was "bold" in its evangelistic activities but "secretive" in its practices, with evangelists sneaking into other Christian churches to attend their services, persuade others to convert to Xintiandi.

"I suspect Xintiandi will not disclose the movements of its followers who have come into contact with case No. 31 and will not fully cooperate with the government's tracking efforts, " Shen said, "They are worried that this will reveal their secret missionary activities, which is really worrying. "

Hwang Eui-jong, a pastor who has studied the new world church, also told The New York Times that members of the church are now targeting Young Koreans, not only for free, for reading divination, there will also be personality tests and foreign language classes.

In Korean Christian circles, the New World Church does not welcome. In 2014, the Korean Council of Christian supervision designated the Church as "heresy, " and the Korean Christian Federation issued a notice in 2016 asking believers to guard against the church's "erosion. ". Since then, the United Kingdom, New Zealand, India and other places have issued a reminder of the Christian community, some parts of China has also issued a ban on the Church's announcement.

Even South Korea's central epidemic prevention department, in an english-language circular on February 19, called the new World Church "cult" . Family members of some members of the congregation "complained" to the media that the church was not being run. 60-year-old Moon Yoo-ja said she had been trying to "save" her daughter for years, "Once people join, they tend to give up their studies and jobs, and some housewives run away from home and abandon their husbands and children. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The orange text reads: The same Korean heresy, named Xintiandi, Source: The English website of the Korean Central Epidemic Prevention Department

Huang Yiying explained that the new heaven and Earth Church followers actually know these "notoriety" , so often will hide their identity, even parents will not tell. After case No. 31 was confirmed, there were rumors on South Korean social media that members of the church had been told to continue their small-scale sermons in private and to deny any contact with the church if asked by the authorities.

The New World Church denied this, saying it had punished those responsible. Lee Man-Hee also on the 21st urged worshippers to "follow the instructions of the government" and cut back on meetings and convert to online sermons. "nearly 300,000 believers are earnestly praying to God for the end of the new pneumonia outbreak, " an official from Daegu told the central daily on the same day

In an internal letter published that day, Lee Man-Hee also encouraged everyone to "win this test" together. "Let us overcome temptation and deceit, deepen our faith, and we will win, " he wrote. "When night falls, the light will come. Faith will bear witness to us. No storm can rob us of our hearts and our faith. "
